{
  "text": "Monte Carlo (MC) simulations were performed in Igor Pro (Version 6, Wavemetrics, Lake Oswego, OR) using modifications to code previously developed to obtain estimates for the coarse parameters of the mechanical unfolding energy landscape for polyproteins containing two different protein domains [CITATION_1] . Each protein domain is assumed to unfold via a two-state, all-or-none process, given by the following adaptation of the Zhurkov-Bell model:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "44355499"
